Analysis: Average St. Charles CUSD 303 teacher compensation is $87,666

Schools

By LGIS News Service | Dec 11, 2018

AddThis Sharing Sidebar
Share to Facebook
, Number of shares
Share to TwitterShare to Reddit
, Number of shares
More AddThis Share options
, Number of shares
Hide
Show

The average teacher at St. Charles CUSD 303 received $87,666 in total compensation in the 2015-2016 school year for working nine months, according to an analysis of Illinois State Board of Education (ISBE) and Teachers Retirement System (TRS) records by the Kane County Reporter. 

The analysis covers 1,387 district employees who received a collective $121.6 million in 2015-2016.

The total compensation number was calculated by combining all the employeesâ€™ base salary for nine months, cost of benefits (at 30 percent), paid sick days and their taxpayer-funded pension contribution.

The pension contribution was 37 percent of each employee's base salary in 2015-2016, according to TRS.

Public school employees pay into the state pension system approximately 3 percent of what they stand to collect in retirement, or $30,000 for each $1 million received. Taxpayers make up the difference.

Of the employee pay packages analyzed, 554 of the 1,387 (40 percent) received more than $100,000; and 25  earned more than $200,000, including top-compensated District Superintendent Donald Schlomann ($449,015) and six teachers.
